<div class="container">
  <div class="page-head">
    <h1>Features</h1>
    <p class="lede">Cueport reads your Serato library, lets you edit in a local working layer, and pushes changes back on approval. View the release notes to learn more about the current build.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="feature-list">
    <article class="feature">
      <div class="feature-head">
        <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 6h6l2 2h8v10a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H4z"/><path d="M4 6v12"/><path d="M8 12h8"/><path d="M8 16h5"/></svg>
        </span>
        <h3>Serato library reader</h3>
      </div>
      <p>Cueport reads crates, subcrates, tracks, BPM, key, and color labels straight from your <code>_Serato_</code> folder on disk.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="feature">
      <div class="feature-head">
        <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 18V6"/><path d="M18 18V6"/><path d="M6 12h12"/><path d="M9 9l3 3-3 3"/><path d="M14 8h4"/><path d="M14 16h4"/></svg>
        </span>
        <h3>Cue points and track notes</h3>
      </div>
      <p>Cueport reads hot cues from each MP3's Serato Markers and uses the Comment field as the track note.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="feature">
      <div class="feature-head">
        <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 7h14"/><path d="M5 12h10"/><path d="M5 17h7"/><path d="M16 15l3 3"/><path d="M19 15l-3 3"/></svg>
        </span>
        <h3>Local editing layer</h3>
      </div>
      <p>Cueport stages your cue point edits, note changes, and new collections in a local database with a clear sync status on every entity.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="feature">
      <div class="feature-head">
        <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 20V7"/><path d="M7 12l5-5 5 5"/><path d="M5 20h14"/><path d="M5 16v4"/><path d="M19 16v4"/></svg>
        </span>
        <h3>Publish on approval</h3>
      </div>
      <p>Cueport writes your staged edits back to your Serato MP3s and crate files only when you choose to publish. Until then, Serato stays untouched.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="feature">
      <div class="feature-head">
        <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="8"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/><path d="M12 4v3"/><path d="M18.5 12H16"/><path d="M12 20v-3"/><path d="M5.5 12H8"/></svg>
        </span>
        <h3>Local audio playback</h3>
      </div>
      <p>Cueport plays tracks from your local files alongside the waveform, beatgrid, and your hot cues, so you can audition without leaving the library.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="feature">
      <div class="feature-head">
        <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3l7 3v5c0 5-3 8-7 10-4-2-7-5-7-10V6z"/><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-5"/><path d="M8 18h8"/></svg>
        </span>
        <h3>Backups and restore points</h3>
      </div>
      <p>Cueport duplicates <code>_Serato_</code> into Application Support after you link it and takes a restore point before every publish so any push can be rolled back.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</div>
